24:57.820 --> 25:08.000
we try to keep it a happy family, And I've seen a lot less of the blood feud
type masquerades than I have of the happy family type masquerades because

25:08.000 --> 25:15.340
usually everybody's there for a good time and they're all there for the same
purpose, to bring it to life. And as long as everybody's after the same thing,

25:15.480 --> 25:25.740
it's all fun. The only major problems that we have with masquerades is a lot of
conventions slough them off as, oh, well, we have to do this, and they really

25:25.740 --> 25:33.340
don't know what they're doing. and the biggest tragedies are when the
contestants are mistreated by the convention because the convention really

25:33.340 --> 25:42.960
doesn't care about the contestants and what they're doing and they really don't
care if it's well run and the masquerade's just kind of an afterthought. And

25:42.960 --> 25:53.600
that's the only time I've seen any real problems. Because most of these people
have worked quite a while to put their... A good example, which is a good

25:53.600 --> 26:02.600
example of a lot of things going wrong with the convention, was the Ultimate
Fantasy and Houston Convention, which was held in Houston just recently. It's

26:02.600 --> 26:11.300
already gotten in a lot of the magazines for the fiasco of the Ultimate Fantasy,
but a little-known tragedy that people don't know about is at one time it was

26:11.300 --> 26:22.860
scheduled that there was to be a masquerade, and we went, and there were a lot
of really wonderful costumes that showed up, and costumes that could have won on

26:22.860 --> 26:32.740
a regional level. and what turned out is there almost wasn't a masquerade at
all. It was kind of a joke. There was no official judges. Fortunately, by the

26:32.740 --> 26:41.240
good graces of Richard Penny, who with his wife, Wendy, they do the Elfquest
books, he showed up, got a couple other people to join with him, and they went

26:41.240 --> 26:49.100
ahead and did judging and announced a winner and so forth. But the convention
itself had sort of washed its hands of the whole thing and was just going to

26:49.100 --> 26:56.100
leave the masqueraders you're standing there with a rock band playing in the
background, when what they'd come to do was the masquerade, not dance in

26:56.100 --> 27:06.380
costume, you can do that on Halloween at any local disco, but it worked out
because again, the pros worked with the costumers to try and make it work, and

27:06.380 --> 27:15.820
although there were no prizes, at least there was a costume contest and there
was an award, and people didn't feel quite so cheated, but the con had just kind

27:15.820 --> 27:29.060
of sloughed it off. I don't want to open a can of worms but there is a
controversy about weapons in the costumers. Is that just kind of a mini-bruhaha?

27:29.460 --> 27:39.760
Actually there is a big deal about weapons but it generally has nothing to do
with the masquerade because unless the masquerade is very poorly run they

27:39.760 --> 27:46.520
usually have enough space where you can do pretty well anything you want and if
you kill yourself on stage that's your tough luck. It's a good idea when using

27:46.520 --> 27:54.180
weapons, if you're going to do anything with a weapon, for God's sake,
choreograph it until you know absolutely perfectly what you're doing before you

27:54.180 --> 28:04.080
ever get up on stage and flourish a weapon. The weapons brouhaha is mainly over
weapons being worn on costumes in the halls. Now, we don't have as much a

28:04.080 --> 28:12.000
problem with it here in the Southwest as they do other places, but the flack
that's coming down from other places has reached here. Basically, what happens

28:12.000 --> 28:20.860
is you have a lot of kids who get a hold of a sword, and they throw it on their
Conan costume, and they draw it in the halls and so forth. We've managed to stop

28:20.860 --> 28:29.240
most of that, because there are simple rules of courtesy, which can be observed,
and weapons are strictly, most of us observe weapons, as strictly a piece of

28:29.240 --> 28:36.860
jewelry that is worn with a costume to complete it. And if you look at it that
way, it's very safe, and you never draw it in public, except with permission by

28:36.860 --> 28:45.100
all around, and you certainly never do duels in the hallway, Duels are strictly
for the masquerade or join a society like the creative anachronisms where you

28:45.100 --> 28:55.140
can fight if you really want to fight. A lot of conventions, rather than ban
them, have instead instituted a policy that if you draw it where you're not

28:55.140 --> 29:02.720
supposed to, or if you threaten some with it where you're not supposed to, you
lose it for the duration of the convention. The ones who have done that and who

29:02.720 --> 29:11.280
have let groups like the society enforce their rules, who have a very strict
code of honor concerning weapons, haven't had any problem. And the main problem

29:11.280 --> 29:20.880
isn't with the normal fans and the people who do costuming and who are serious
about what they do. The main problem is with the kids or the people off the

29:20.880 --> 29:28.080
street who think weapons are a neat, fun toy and, oh, boy, now we can sword
fight because we're at a convention or, oh, boy, now we can shoot somebody with

29:28.080 --> 29:34.880
a water pistol because we're at a convention. It's not allowed anywhere else and
it's not allowed at a convention either. Conventioning does not give you an

29:34.880 --> 29:42.880
excuse to do these kind of bad things and it's a few who are trying to ruin it
for the many. and that's basically all the weapons thing is. The best weapons

29:42.880 --> 29:53.820
policy I've seen for a major convention is what Chicago had. I did not attend
Chicago but I did read their weapons policy and basically it's stated keep your

29:53.820 --> 30:02.420
blade, if you're wearing a blade, keep it sheathed at all times unless you were
showing the blade in which case you have to do it in a basically secluded spot,

30:02.420 --> 30:10.120
make sure there's no one around who could be startled by your drawing the blade
and make sure they know you're doing it and strictly to show not in a defense or

30:10.120 --> 30:19.740
attack position, but in a showing position where it could not possibly be
construed as a threat. Even then, the con had the right, if they thought you

30:19.740 --> 30:29.800
were drawing it in a threatening manner, to confiscate it. No weapons that shot
things, no water guns, no frisbee guns, nothing that shot any kind of actual

30:29.800 --> 30:39.880
substance, even if it was just water, nothing that looked like a real gun,
because there have been occasions when people have brought real weapons into a

30:39.880 --> 30:47.620
hotel. Even if they had nothing to do with the convention, it caused problems,
so no replicas that looked like real guns, even if it does go with the costume,

30:49.080 --> 30:57.420
and courtesy about how you wear them so that you don't slam into people's legs
because your sword's stuck out behind you, and no livestock.

